'''Rick Berry''' (born [[June 2]], [[1950s#1953|1953]] in [[Wikipedia:San Bernardino, California|San Bernardino, California]])<ref name="Speculative" /> is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] artist who digitally painted the covers of two ''[[Star Wars]]'' paperbacks in the year [[2000]]: ''[[The New Jedi Order: Agents of Chaos I: Hero's Trial|Hero's Trial]]'' and ''[[The New Jedi Order: Agents of Chaos II: Jedi Eclipse|Jedi Eclipse]]'', the two installments of [[James Luceno]]'s ''[[Agents of Chaos Duology]]''.

As a digital painter, Berry is credited with creating the world's first digitally painted book cover in [[1984]] for [[Wikipedia:William Gibson|William Gibson's]] ''[[Wikipedia:Neuromancer|Neuromancer]]''. His art is exhibited in museums and galleries all over the world and can be found in the private collections of [[Wikipedia:Neil Gaiman|Neil Gaiman]], [[Wikipedia:Stephen King|Stephen King]] and [[Wikipedia:George R. R. Martin|George R. R. Martin]].<ref name="IX">{{WebCite|url=https://ixgallery.com/artists/rickberry/|text=Rick Berry|work=IX Gallery|archivedate=20260117230929}}</ref>

